{
  "texts": [
    "Components that cause changes or maintenance in other components are known as \"Tools,\" while the affected components are called \"Objects.\"",
    "These relationships can be categorized as either useful or harmful, depending on the designer's perspective (Rantanen et al., 2017).",
    "Therefore, in the third step, the designer should analyze the relationships and determine which ones are useful or harmful from their perspective.",
    "According to TRIZ principles, behind each harmful relationship lies Table 2.",
    "Interaction extraction example TEXT A house is a building that serves as a dwelling for individuals or families."
  ]
}